# Testing BACK_FUTURE
 
Astro static site for educational `back to the future` content. Build is fully static (`output: "static"` in `astro.config.mjs`), so any test can run against `dist/` via a simple HTTP server.
 
## Vercel preview is SSO-protected
 
The Vercel preview URL (e.g. `back-future-git-<branch>-skords-01s-projects.vercel.app`) requires Vercel SSO. Anonymous `curl` returns **HTTP 401**. Do NOT attempt to test against Vercel preview — go local.
 
## Local test workflow
 
From the repo root, with the PR branch checked out:
 
```bash
npm install        # only if node_modules is stale
npm run build      # produces dist/ — runs astro check + astro build + pagefind
python3 -m http.server 4321 --directory dist > /tmp/preview.log 2>&1 &
```
 
Then check pages: `curl -s http://localhost:4321/2024/`. URLs use trailing slashes (`/<year>/`, not `/<year>`). Stop the server with `pkill -f "http.server 4321"`.
 
## Epoch snapshot data model
 
- Files: `content/epoch/<year>.json` for each epoch year (currently 1995, 2000, 2005, 2010, 2012, 2014, 2015, 2020, 2024).
- Schema: `{ year: number, items: [{ k: string, v: string }, ...] }`.
- Rendered by `src/components/ThenAside.astro` as `<dt>{item.k}</dt><dd>{item.v}</dd>`.
- Used on every `/<year>/` page via `src/pages/[year].astro`.
 
### Fallback behaviour
 
`ThenAside` picks the **nearest** epoch by absolute distance, with ties going to the earlier year:
 
```ts
epochEntries.slice().sort((a, b) => {
  const da = Math.abs(a.data.year - year);
  const db = Math.abs(b.data.year - year);
  return da - db || a.data.year - b.data.year;
});
```
 
So `/1998/` shows the **2000** snapshot (distance 2 vs distance 3 to 1995). `/1997/` is equidistant (2 to 1995, 3 to 2000) → also picks 1995 because of the tiebreaker. Useful to test both an in-between year and an exact-epoch year.
 
## Grep gotchas
 
- Astro encodes apostrophes as `&#39;` in rendered HTML. When searching for raw values that contain `'` (e.g. `McDonald's`), grep for the entity form.
- Cyrillic content is UTF-8; use `grep -F` for literal multibyte strings to avoid regex surprises.
 
## Useful commands
 
```bash
# Lint + typecheck + build (locally, no CI needed)
npm run lint           # ESLint + Prettier + markdownlint
npm run typecheck      # tsc --noEmit
npm run build          # full Astro build with content validation
npm run validate:content   # JSON schema validation only
npm test               # unit tests
```
 
## CI notes
 
- The `verify` job runs Playwright e2e Smoke tests. As of May 2026, mobile-375px and year-flow tests are flaky/broken on `main` (same failures regardless of PR contents). Don't block merging on them when the PR is content-only or changes don't touch those flows.
- `Link check` and the Vercel preview deployment are the most reliable signals for content/build regressions.
 
## Scope of GUI testing
 
- Year pages (`/<year>/`) — ThenAside, YearHero, FactTimeline, SubjectFilters
- Quiz (`/quiz/`)
- Search (Pagefind, opens via the search icon in the nav)
- Footer (SERGEANT_GROUP block)
- About (`/about/`), Methodology (`/metodologia/`), Themes (`/themes/`)
- Era pages (`/era/<slug>/`), Subject pages (`/subject/<id>/`), Fact pages (`/fact/<slug>/`)
 
## Devin Secrets Needed
 
- `Git_PAT` — only if direct GitHub authentication is needed when the git-manager proxy returns 403 (used to push branches and read PR metadata). Format: `git push "https://x-access-token:${Git_PAT}@github.com/Skords-01/BACK_FUTURE.git" <branch>:<branch>`.
